      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;"Just because they make a pvp server doesn't mean you have to play on it."&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Well, that's the problem, isn't it?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Only a very small minority ever did play on the PvP servers.&amp;nbsp; That's why they were condensed into one and the reason why Rallos rules were chosen is because there were more people on Rallos than on any of the other servers. (and hey, I played on Rallos and I had a lot of fun but that's me)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;People keep talking about the success of PvP servers.&amp;nbsp; I've never seen it.&amp;nbsp; Now, true, I started around Velious launch but back then they still had server numbers.&amp;nbsp; Morell-Thule was always a low density server but 99% of the time we were higher than any of the zeks.&amp;nbsp; There may have been an hour in prime time every now and then when maybe one of the zeks had more than us but that was it.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;When numbers were taken away but the servers could still be ranked by population, Sullon was ALWAYS the lowest density server.&amp;nbsp; That's right, the number 1 slot was the smallest population of all the servers.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I understand the desire to have a new PvP server, really I do.&amp;nbsp; But many of us (including, I think SOE people) need some proof of the viability of the server before they open it.&amp;nbsp; The best chance of that is to get people to come back and go red on Combine.&amp;nbsp; Other proponents of PvP server say that people won't spend money for things they don't want (ie, going red on a blue server).&amp;nbsp; I don't look at it that way, I see it as a way to invest in something I want.&amp;nbsp; It is $20 for a Titanium pack and a free month.&amp;nbsp; It's $15 to reactivate an account.&amp;nbsp; Heck, our household non-eq but related expenses are more than that.&amp;nbsp; Subscribe to Allakhazam here, throw some money to EQTraders, this and that and the other thing.&amp;nbsp; I donated $35 to Wikipedia because one day when i was looking up they had a polite little message.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;$15-20 for something you believe in is nothing.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
